he Rev. J. J. Webb\nconducted the funeral services.\njuries consisted of a few bruises and\nscratches.\nTwo coaches did not leave the rails, a\nsleeper and a special car occupied by j\nVice President E. Ford of the Alabama\nand Vicksburg railroad. The derailment\nwas caused by recent heavy rains soften\ning the roadbed. The train was bound\nfrom Memphis for New Orleans.\nPassengers suffered principally from\nsix hours spent in the open country\nwaiting for relief.\nSTATE SECURES TITLE TO\nSITE FOR MODEL PRISON\nj Montgomery, March 9.\u2014(Special.)\u2014Camp\nSheridan passed into the hands of the\nstate today with the formal delivery of\nthe deed to Governor Kilby by Mayor\n\\V. A. Gunter, Jr., of Montgomery and\nthe payment by the state of *50,000 for\nthe site. In addition to this amount,\nthe chamber of commerce paid the city\n*0,000. The state is already maturing\nplans for the erection of a model prison\non the site to take the place of the\nprison and cotton mills at Speigner. Mar\ntin J. Lide, Birmingham architect, con\nferred with the board of control about\nthe plans during the day.\n11\nCaleb Powers Sued\nBy Associated Press\nWashington, March 9.\u2014Caleb Powers,\nformer member of Congress, whose\ntriatk In connection with the killing of\nformer Governor Goebel of Kentucky\nsome years ago attracted nation-wide\nattention, was sued here today\u2018by his\nwife. Anna M. D. Powers, for limited di\nvorce. The petition, filed in the Dis\ntrict of Columbia supreme court,\ncharged cruelty and non-support. Jus\ntice Stafford Issued a rule against the\ndefendant, who now lives in Washing\nton, to show cause on March 18 why\nhe should not be required to pay tem\nporary alimony pending the outcome of\nthe proceedings.\nWORST OF DEPRESSION\nOVER, DECLARES FORD\nBy Associated Press\nDetroit. Mich., March 9.--The worst of\nthe business depression Is over, Henry\nFord, the automobile manufacturer, satit\ntoday. He declared business was im\nproving steadily in Detroit, and that sim\nilar pains should result in other parts of\nthe country \u00aboon.\n\u2022\u2019Different conditions will prevail after\nthe readjustment than before the war,1'\nhe said. \"There will bo more economy\nin every way, but the volume of business\nwill continually prow.\n\"The condition which is just passing\nand disarmament,\u201d Mr. Ford continued,\n\u2022\u2018than all the writing and speech-making*\nand parleying in the world. The waf*\nbrought on a false prosperity. What has\nfollowed the war has proved it was\nfalse.\u201d\nProduction of the Ford factories\n\u201cpretty nearly\u201d on a pre-war basis, he\nadded.\nGazelles, though extremely shy. can\nbe easily domesticated if captured\nwhen young.\nChildren Cry\nFOR FLETCHER\u2019S\nCASTORIA\n\"\"3\nFREE\nTry a Crisp, Delicious\nDoughnut or Slice of\nCake With Our\nCompliments\nft\nFREE\nTry a Crisp Delicious\nDoughnut or Slice of\nCake With Our\nCompliments\nI\nI\nijfeM m\nMr. Edward P. Vieh\nthe man who originally\nopened the Barker System\nof Bakeries in Birming\nham, will have the per\nsonal supervision of this\nstore. Mr. H. L. Bailey\nwill also be here as assist\nant manager. Both of\nthese gentlemen extend\nto their old-time friends\nand customers a personal\ninvitation to visit and in\nspect the Barker store.\nThey are bringing back\nthe high quality and splen\ndid service that made the\nBarker System famous.\nI! You\u2019ll Love\nthe Barker\nLoaf>\nHere\u2019s a delicious bread\u2014\nthe rich brown, crisp crust\n\u2014the wholesome, zest\nful body of the bread, the\nlikeable taste and flavor\nmakes this a bread that\nonce used becomes a\nsteady occupant of your\n4\ntable.\nTry it once and you will\nbuy it ahvays.\nAfter being closed for a few days for the purpose of making va\nrious alterations and improvements, the Barker Bakery, at 1919\nThird avenue, will reopen this morning and extends to the public\na cordial invitation to inspect this completely renovated and\nthoroughly modern bake shop. Everything is spic, span and\nspotless, every improved method and item of equipment is em\nployed. Come in and let us show you through and convince you\nthat here is indeed the home of QUALITY.\nOld-Time Service\nK\nand Quality\nThe old-time quality and smiling, courteous service, that made\nso many friends among the housewives of Birmingham, will be\nrestored under the new management. The original Barker pat\nent formula will be scrupulously adhered to, the celebrated\n\u201cOccident\u201d flour, conceded to be the best ground, will be used.\nThe public may now buy Barker products with the full assur\nance that an unsurpassable quality will be rigidly maintained in\nevery detail. You may buy in perfect confidence Barker Bread,\nCakes, Pies and Pastries.\n1919 Third Avenue\nSupervision Mr. Edward P. Vieh\n4\nOpening Day\nSpecials\nAs a special open\ning day value we\nwill sell you today\none dozen dough\nnuts and one loaf\nof bread for\nComes Clean\nFrom the Oven\nto You\nYou cannot buy better\nbread than Barkers, for\nbetter bread cannot be\nmade. The finest quality\nMinnesota wheat is em\nployed in making the\nflour from which it is\nmade, and the very best\ningredients are used.\nIts purity and cleanliness\nis safeguarded in every\noperation until it gets to\nyour table.\nI","height":"28236","width":"19808"}}
